# CADEX INDEX.map — symbol-level artifact index
# The agent queries this BEFORE reading any file.
# Only files matching the current task's keywords are loaded.
# Hash mismatch = file changed since last index = re-index before loading.
#
# VOLATILITY values:
#   durable   — stable, rarely changes (interfaces, core logic)
#   volatile  — changes frequently (handlers, controllers, tests)
#   archived  — no longer active, kept for reference only
#
# USAGE by agent:
#   1. Extract keywords from current task
#   2. Match keywords against each file's keyword list
#   3. Load ONLY matched files — and ONLY the matched symbols within them
#   4. Verify hash matches file on disk before using stored symbol locations
#   5. If hash mismatch: re-read file, update this index, then proceed

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SCHEMA — one block per file
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# [file/path/name.ext]
# purpose:    [one line — what this file does]
# keywords:   [comma-separated retrieval terms]
# volatility: durable | volatile | archived
# last_task:  [task_id that last modified this file]
# symbols:
#   [SymbolName]  @sha256:[8-char-hash]  lines:[start]-[end]  # [brief note]

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# EXAMPLE ENTRIES (delete and replace with your own)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

